<lb corresp="#b8"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>nne</w><w>īkäṃ</w><w>piś</w><w>po</w><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... was staying in ... He saw ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1949"/><citedRange>II, 11</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(what to do with this) body, this dripping ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... here only you carry (to the) cemetery ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... always impurities ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... at exactly that time ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the assembly. [103d] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (of the beings) having carried ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... all twenty-five ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">Uv 1.36</note><note type="philcomment" subtype="General_remarks">Anityavarga (I), part two. The fact that this belongs to this section is indicated by the quotation of Uv I 36, but it is not possible to determine recto and verso side with any certainty, since only 4 lines with a single strophe-number are preserved.</note><note type="remarks">The original manuscript is missing, but was a small fragment of only 4 lines.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="parallel_texts">
            <head>Sanskrit parallel</head>
            <p><ref type="ms" target="#a2"/> corresponds to Uv. I, 36: 
kim anena śarīreṇa sravatā pūtinā sadā 
nityaṃ rogābhibhūtena jarā maraṇa bhīruṇā</p>
            <p>Alas! this body will soon lie on the earth unnoticed, empty</p>
         </div>
